        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pinion shims are available in the following thickness:</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">IN.</emph>.005 .010 .030
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">MM</emph>.127 .254 .762
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1"></para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If exact shim measurement cannot be achieved with the available shims, use shims required to
                        approximate correct pinion position.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position shims on carrier housing so oil return holes align properly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401457">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401457" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401457" filename="../figg14/g1401457.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Align Oil Return Holes</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be certain mounting surfaces and shims are free of dirt and nicks, or leaks may occur and
                        pinion position can be affected.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install pinion and pinion cage assembly into carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401458">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401458" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401458" filename="../figg14/g1401458.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Pinion Cage Assembly Into Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Studs can be used to assist in alignment.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten pinion cage to carrier bolts to 160 to 180 ft-lbs. (217 to 244 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401459">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401459" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401459" filename="../figg14/g1401459.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Tighten Pinion Cage To Carrier Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">An alternative to using the pinion setting gauges is to follow the procedure described in
                the
                <hotlnk document="s14014_23.xml" xrefid="hl1401411">Pinion Setting Chart</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
